WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:12.000
My name is Valery Kapsar. I will read you a course on financial management. I am a professor at the Moscow Business School.

00:12.000 --> 00:18.000
Today's topic is the financial documents of the enterprise.

00:19.000 --> 00:22.000
We will consider two main questions.

00:22.000 --> 00:28.000
The first one is to see what financial documents are the main ones at the enterprise.

00:28.000 --> 00:32.000
We will consider the main document, the enterprise balance.

00:32.000 --> 00:41.000
And the second question is to analyze the financial accounting, which is seen from the financial documents.

00:41.000 --> 00:46.000
So, let's start with our first question.

00:46.000 --> 00:55.000
Financial accounting is a collection of information about the funds of the enterprise, the sources of these funds and their movements.

00:55.000 --> 01:02.000
The main question is why do we need financial accounting?

01:02.000 --> 01:10.000
Why do all enterprises in our country and in any other country of the world prepare this accounting?

01:10.000 --> 01:13.000
Who needs it and how much?

01:13.000 --> 01:17.000
Let's think about this question together.

01:17.000 --> 01:25.000
Who needs financial accounting? Who gets interesting results from it?

01:30.000 --> 01:32.000
You are absolutely right.

01:32.000 --> 01:37.000
First of all, the enterprise owner needs financial accounting.

01:38.000 --> 01:44.000
The enterprise owner is the most interested person in the successful business.

01:44.000 --> 01:55.000
He is very interested in whether he invested his money correctly, whether he is doing a business that brings him the most income.

01:55.000 --> 02:04.000
Therefore, the enterprise owner studies and is ready to consider all the financial information that he receives every day.

02:05.000 --> 02:11.000
The second most interested person is the manager who manages the enterprise.

02:11.000 --> 02:20.000
Currently, more and more managers, the first members of the enterprise, are not the owners of the enterprise.

02:20.000 --> 02:23.000
This is a common trend all over the world.

02:23.000 --> 02:30.000
The owners gradually leave the management of the enterprise, transferring the management to high-level professionals.

02:31.000 --> 02:38.000
A high-level professional is interested in the fact that the owner highly appreciates his work.

02:38.000 --> 02:42.000
What is the assessment of his work? The success of the enterprise.

02:42.000 --> 02:51.000
Therefore, for the manager, the results that the enterprise achieves are the most important point that characterizes his activity.

02:52.000 --> 03:02.000
Therefore, the manager draws financial information, studies it, and makes management decisions to make the enterprise work even better.

03:03.000 --> 03:06.000
Who else needs financial accounting?

03:07.000 --> 03:14.000
You are absolutely right to notice that financial accounting is needed by the state structure.

03:14.000 --> 03:27.000
I would like to draw your attention to the fact that the state in all countries of the world obliges the enterprise to provide financial accounting to the state bodies.

03:28.000 --> 03:33.000
There are two state bodies that are particularly interested in financial accounting.

03:34.000 --> 03:37.000
The first is the Tax Inspection.

03:37.000 --> 03:44.000
The Tax Inspection is responsible for the collection of taxes, it monitors the enterprise's activities,

03:44.000 --> 03:52.000
and therefore it is the most important responsibility to work with financial accounting, to receive it, to analyze it.

03:53.000 --> 04:00.000
The second state body that is interested in financial accounting, not only financial, but in a broader sense,

04:00.000 --> 04:10.000
is the State Bodies, which study the statistics of the enterprise, the industry, and the state as a whole.

04:11.000 --> 04:17.000
Therefore, they also need the accounting that comes from the enterprise.

04:18.000 --> 04:25.000
I dare to assure you that the accounting that the enterprise prepares, in terms of accounting for the accounting,

04:25.000 --> 04:30.000
is the accounting that is primarily needed by the state bodies.

04:31.000 --> 04:38.000
It is designed to be the accounting that is needed for these state bodies.

04:39.000 --> 04:45.000
We will return to this question several times in our lectures, and mention it several times,

04:46.000 --> 04:51.000
but today I am focusing on this most important point in our material.

04:52.000 --> 04:58.000
The next people who need to know the financial accounting of the enterprise are investors and creditors.

04:59.000 --> 05:04.000
Imagine that you are the company that invests in the enterprise.

05:05.000 --> 05:13.000
You are very interested in how successfully those who invest their capital are doing business.

05:13.000 --> 05:19.000
It is very important for you to know their financial accounting, to analyze it,

05:20.000 --> 05:25.000
and to be sure that the invested funds will return to you in a hundred percent.

05:26.000 --> 05:30.000
The same approach is pursued by bankers.

05:31.000 --> 05:36.000
They issue loans to enterprises, and it is very important for them to get the loan back.

05:36.000 --> 05:40.000
This is the result of the bankers' work, their professionalism,

05:41.000 --> 05:45.000
and, in the end, it is their business to earn money by issuing loans.

05:46.000 --> 05:50.000
Therefore, bankers are very careful about who they give loans to.

05:51.000 --> 05:55.000
It is especially important, because you need to remember that loans are primarily used by those

05:56.000 --> 06:00.000
who do not have enough money for one reason or another.

06:00.000 --> 06:06.000
Therefore, there can be those who already have a very difficult financial situation.

06:07.000 --> 06:11.000
They will not be able to save a single loan, but they will grab the straw and try to get it back

06:12.000 --> 06:16.000
in order to pull their enterprise out of a difficult situation.

06:17.000 --> 06:26.000
Bankers are very careful about giving loans only to those who are able to return it.

06:27.000 --> 06:33.000
The next people who are interested in the financial situation are business partners.

06:34.000 --> 06:40.000
Imagine that you run a business, your enterprise runs a business with a particular enterprise.

06:41.000 --> 06:48.000
You jointly build a business, plan, make purchases, invest money.

06:49.000 --> 06:54.000
Aren't you interested in how stable the enterprise you work with is?

06:54.000 --> 07:00.000
If it burns, you will burn as well.

07:01.000 --> 07:06.000
It is very important to know the financial situation of your business partner.

07:07.000 --> 07:15.000
Therefore, before starting a large project, you must study the financial situation of your partner.

07:16.000 --> 07:19.000
But even if you do not start a joint large project,

07:19.000 --> 07:27.000
but you just buy, make purchases, or sell goods to this enterprise,

07:28.000 --> 07:35.000
because you plan your business based on the fact that your partner will constantly make these purchases,

07:36.000 --> 07:39.000
you need a stable financial situation for this.

07:40.000 --> 07:45.000
Therefore, the interest in financial accountability is very appropriate.

07:45.000 --> 07:51.000
And the last place, although not the last in importance,

07:52.000 --> 07:56.000
is the interest in the financial accountability of the enterprise.

07:57.000 --> 07:59.000
This is shown by the employees of this enterprise.

08:00.000 --> 08:02.000
But not always.

08:03.000 --> 08:08.000
There are cases in the life of an enterprise when it has a very difficult financial situation.

08:09.000 --> 08:13.000
And when it can soon go bankrupt,

08:14.000 --> 08:19.000
and then all the employees of this enterprise will be behind the gates.

08:20.000 --> 08:26.000
In this case, employees are often fired without a salary.

08:27.000 --> 08:31.000
At the same time, there are long-term delays in the salary.

08:32.000 --> 08:34.000
Employees are very worried in these cases.

08:34.000 --> 08:38.000
It is very important for them to know how stable this enterprise is,

08:39.000 --> 08:41.000
whether it will survive, whether it will return.

08:42.000 --> 08:45.000
After all, they are patriots, they continue to work at their enterprise.

08:46.000 --> 08:48.000
They hope and believe in this enterprise.

08:49.000 --> 08:52.000
They really want to know that everything is fine in this enterprise.

08:53.000 --> 08:59.000
They are ready to ask every day, every week, if everything will be fine.

09:00.000 --> 09:07.000
So we saw who needs financial accountability at the enterprise.

09:08.000 --> 09:12.000
Thus, financial accountability is not an empty sound, not bare numbers on paper.

09:13.000 --> 09:19.000
Financial accountability is a business and a life of a large number of people

09:20.000 --> 09:23.000
that are connected by the business threads with this enterprise.

09:23.000 --> 09:26.000
That is why we need to know financial accountability,

09:27.000 --> 09:32.000
study it, understand it, read it, evaluate it and draw conclusions.

09:33.000 --> 09:37.000
This is what our lecture is dedicated to.

09:38.000 --> 09:40.000
Now let's talk about financial accountability.

09:41.000 --> 09:47.000
What requirements are presented to it by all the above-mentioned people

09:48.000 --> 09:51.000
who are interested in studying financial accountability?

09:51.000 --> 09:55.000
Let's list them and discuss the most important ones.

09:56.000 --> 09:58.000
Let's open their contents.

09:59.000 --> 10:02.000
Financial accountability must be objective.

10:03.000 --> 10:05.000
It must be truthful.

10:06.000 --> 10:10.000
It should not contain lies, it should not contain embellishments.

10:11.000 --> 10:17.000
Since everyone studies financial accountability and perceives it as a pure coin,

10:17.000 --> 10:22.000
it should be absolutely truthful.

10:23.000 --> 10:27.000
Unfortunately, it should be noted that business in our country

10:28.000 --> 10:31.000
does not always provide objective financial accountability.

10:32.000 --> 10:37.000
It is the case that business in our country is embellished

10:38.000 --> 10:42.000
with financial accountability, especially for tax services.

10:42.000 --> 10:47.000
Moreover, you can find such attitude of the business leaders

10:48.000 --> 10:51.000
that financial accountability is made for tax services

10:52.000 --> 10:55.000
and the leader is not even interested in financial accountability.

10:56.000 --> 10:58.000
It is so far from reality.

10:59.000 --> 11:01.000
This is a bad attitude to financial accountability.

11:02.000 --> 11:04.000
This is the situation that should be avoided.

11:05.000 --> 11:07.000
Time will put everything in its place.

11:07.000 --> 11:10.000
Taxation in our country will become more or less normal,

11:11.000 --> 11:13.000
civilized as in the rest of the world,

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
and our business will not run away from taxes,

11:17.000 --> 11:20.000
will not hide from taxes, but will honestly pay the small taxes

11:21.000 --> 11:25.000
that should be paid in any civilized country.

11:26.000 --> 11:29.000
Then financial accountability that we are talking about

11:30.000 --> 11:32.000
will become absolutely objective.

11:33.000 --> 11:36.000
It will not contain a single drop of what is not really there.

11:37.000 --> 11:40.000
The main requirement of financial accountability is its neutrality.

11:41.000 --> 11:46.000
It should be neutral, regardless of the interests of a particular business.

11:47.000 --> 11:50.000
It should be ready to accept any subjects

11:51.000 --> 11:54.000
that are interested in financial accountability.

11:55.000 --> 11:58.000
It should reflect the interests of all these subjects.

11:59.000 --> 12:02.000
Financial accountability should be independent.

12:02.000 --> 12:06.000
It should be as objective as possible,

12:07.000 --> 12:11.000
regardless of the people who prepare it.

12:12.000 --> 12:16.000
Recently, there has been a trend in our country

12:17.000 --> 12:20.000
when accounting is transferred to outsourcing.

12:21.000 --> 12:23.000
When there are specialized companies

12:24.000 --> 12:26.000
that deal with accounting.

12:27.000 --> 12:31.000
It is worth noting that if an independent company

12:32.000 --> 12:36.000
that does not serve its own business,

12:37.000 --> 12:39.000
does not serve its CEO,

12:40.000 --> 12:42.000
does not conduct an accounting,

12:43.000 --> 12:46.000
then this accounting is largely independent

12:47.000 --> 12:50.000
of the will of the person to do so.

12:51.000 --> 12:53.000
Therefore, it is more objective,

12:54.000 --> 12:56.000
more precise in reflecting information.

12:57.000 --> 13:01.000
The next requirement of accountability is its comparability.

13:02.000 --> 13:05.000
The thing is that the accountability we are talking about

13:06.000 --> 13:08.000
is not necessary on its own.

13:09.000 --> 13:11.000
It is not necessary to put it on a shelf

13:12.000 --> 13:14.000
and let it lie there and get dusty.

13:15.000 --> 13:18.000
Accountability is necessary to conduct analysis

13:19.000 --> 13:22.000
and compare various enterprises

13:23.000 --> 13:25.000
or, within the framework of the same enterprise,

13:26.000 --> 13:28.000
various periods of its business.

13:28.000 --> 13:30.000
To compare various countries,

13:31.000 --> 13:34.000
to consider the development of our own country

13:35.000 --> 13:37.000
in which we live from a business point of view.

13:38.000 --> 13:40.000
But in order to do all this,

13:41.000 --> 13:44.000
all accountability must be similar, comparable.

13:45.000 --> 13:50.000
In this case, they can easily be comparable.

13:51.000 --> 13:53.000
Financial accountability must be periodic.

13:54.000 --> 13:56.000
It cannot be issued every day.

13:56.000 --> 13:58.000
It is not necessary,

13:59.000 --> 14:01.000
because the preparation of this accountability

14:02.000 --> 14:05.000
requires a lot of effort of the workers who prepare it.

14:06.000 --> 14:08.000
But it cannot be issued

14:09.000 --> 14:11.000
in a very long period of time,

14:12.000 --> 14:14.000
let's say, every 10 years.

14:15.000 --> 14:18.000
It is pointless to make management decisions every 10 years.

14:19.000 --> 14:22.000
In 10 years, anything can happen to the enterprise.

14:23.000 --> 14:25.000
It may not live to the next financial accountability.

14:26.000 --> 14:28.000
But it is an optimal regime

14:29.000 --> 14:32.000
in which the financial accountability is prepared.

14:33.000 --> 14:35.000
Financial accountability is made once a quarter,

14:36.000 --> 14:38.000
that is, four times a year.

14:39.000 --> 14:41.000
As a result of the year,

14:42.000 --> 14:44.000
annual financial accountability is made.

14:45.000 --> 14:47.000
The next requirement is the full coverage.

14:48.000 --> 14:50.000
Financial accountability must take into account

14:51.000 --> 14:53.000
all the costs that the enterprise has incurred,

14:53.000 --> 14:55.000
all the costs that the enterprise has incurred,

14:56.000 --> 14:58.000
and all the results that it has achieved.

14:59.000 --> 15:01.000
It must cover everything, reflect everything,

15:02.000 --> 15:05.000
and show all the operations that took place at the enterprise.

15:06.000 --> 15:08.000
It must not leave anything behind.

15:09.000 --> 15:11.000
Financial accountability and shadow economy,

15:12.000 --> 15:14.000
as we see, are incompatible.

15:15.000 --> 15:18.000
Because one assumes the absence of the other.

15:18.000 --> 15:20.000
Financial accountability must be reliable.

15:21.000 --> 15:23.000
The information contained in it

15:24.000 --> 15:26.000
must be true,

15:27.000 --> 15:29.000
must be understandable,

15:30.000 --> 15:32.000
it must cause trust.

15:33.000 --> 15:35.000
Moreover, the information

15:36.000 --> 15:38.000
that is considered in financial accountability

15:39.000 --> 15:41.000
should not be infinitely large.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.000
It should be narrowed down to the level

15:44.000 --> 15:46.000
that is needed to understand

15:47.000 --> 15:49.000
the real financial state of the enterprise.

15:50.000 --> 15:52.000
This is what the next quality

15:53.000 --> 15:55.000
that is presented in financial accountability is about.

15:56.000 --> 15:58.000
It is its significance.

15:59.000 --> 16:01.000
Only significant moments

16:02.000 --> 16:04.000
should be in financial accountability.

16:05.000 --> 16:07.000
What does annual financial accountability include?

16:08.000 --> 16:10.000
Financial accountability prepares the accounting.

16:11.000 --> 16:13.000
Annual financial accountability includes

16:14.000 --> 16:16.000
the following.

16:17.000 --> 16:19.000
Accounting balance, form 1.

16:20.000 --> 16:22.000
Accounting of profits and losses, form 2.

16:23.000 --> 16:26.000
Accounting of capital changes, form 3.

16:27.000 --> 16:30.000
Accounting of money movements, form 4.

16:31.000 --> 16:34.000
Accounting balance application, form 5.

16:35.000 --> 16:37.000
An explanatory note

16:38.000 --> 16:40.000
that analyzes the factors

16:41.000 --> 16:43.000
that led to certain results of the enterprise.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.000
This is the final part of the audit.

16:47.000 --> 16:49.000
In the cases when this audit

16:50.000 --> 16:52.000
is necessary for the enterprise.

16:53.000 --> 16:55.000
Now we will look at

16:56.000 --> 16:58.000
the main document of financial accountability

16:59.000 --> 17:01.000
in more detail.

17:02.000 --> 17:04.000
It is the accounting balance.

17:05.000 --> 17:07.000
Before studying the accounting balance,

17:08.000 --> 17:10.000
I recommend you to hold it in your hands.

17:11.000 --> 17:13.000
One thing is to study it theoretically,

17:14.000 --> 17:16.000
but you should see it in front of you.

17:17.000 --> 17:19.000
On the slide that you see now

17:20.000 --> 17:22.000
you see the general example

17:23.000 --> 17:25.000
of the accounting balance.

17:26.000 --> 17:28.000
It consists of two parts, the left and the right part.

17:29.000 --> 17:31.000
We will talk about it in detail now.

17:32.000 --> 17:34.000
But the most important thing is that

17:35.000 --> 17:37.000
you should hold such an accounting balance in your hands.

17:38.000 --> 17:40.000
Use your own enterprise.

17:41.000 --> 17:43.000
It will be interesting for you to learn

17:44.000 --> 17:46.000
how to use it.

17:47.000 --> 17:49.000
The accounting balance is an open document.

17:50.000 --> 17:52.000
No one hides it.

17:53.000 --> 17:55.000
This document is presented to those who ask for it.

17:56.000 --> 17:58.000
You can turn to your accounting office

17:59.000 --> 18:01.000
and say that studying the course of financial management

18:02.000 --> 18:04.000
and being ready to become a high-class financier

18:05.000 --> 18:07.000
or the head of the enterprise

18:08.000 --> 18:10.000
who understands the activities of the enterprise

18:11.000 --> 18:13.000
and is going to manage it very high quality

18:14.000 --> 18:16.000
requires studying the accounting balance.

18:17.000 --> 18:19.000
No one will refuse you.

18:20.000 --> 18:22.000
You will get the accounting balance

18:23.000 --> 18:25.000
and study it carefully, read it,

18:26.000 --> 18:28.000
you will understand and see a lot of useful information.

18:29.000 --> 18:31.000
What does the accounting balance contain?

18:32.000 --> 18:34.000
The left and the right part.

18:35.000 --> 18:37.000
The left column.

18:38.000 --> 18:40.000
The right column.

18:41.000 --> 18:43.000
The left column shows the assets of the enterprise.

18:44.000 --> 18:46.000
The assets of the enterprise are structured

18:47.000 --> 18:49.000
according to the composition and direction of their use.

18:50.000 --> 18:52.000
The right column shows the same assets,

18:53.000 --> 18:55.000
but structured according to the sources of their financing.

18:56.000 --> 18:58.000
The left and the right part,

18:59.000 --> 19:01.000
I want to draw your attention to,

19:02.000 --> 19:04.000
are the same assets of the enterprise.

19:05.000 --> 19:07.000
The only difference is the cut of these assets.

19:08.000 --> 19:10.000
One cut reflects the direction of use,

19:11.000 --> 19:13.000
and the other cut means

19:14.000 --> 19:16.000
the sources of the resources.

19:17.000 --> 19:19.000
Where did these resources come from

19:20.000 --> 19:22.000
and where were they directed?

19:23.000 --> 19:25.000
It's all simple in the accounting balance.

19:26.000 --> 19:28.000
There is nothing complicated.

19:29.000 --> 19:31.000
The accounting balance also meets the following requirements.

19:32.000 --> 19:34.000
Since these are the same resources,

19:35.000 --> 19:37.000
the left and the right part,

19:38.000 --> 19:40.000
the balance amount of the left part

19:41.000 --> 19:43.000
is equal to the balance amount of the right part.

19:44.000 --> 19:46.000
The balance amount of the right part

19:47.000 --> 19:49.000
is equal to the balance amount of the left part.

19:50.000 --> 19:52.000
Therefore, we can safely say

19:53.000 --> 19:55.000
that the balance amount of all assets

19:56.000 --> 19:58.000
is equal to the balance amount of all balances.

19:59.000 --> 20:01.000
The balances of the enterprise

20:02.000 --> 20:04.000
are the sources of the enterprise's financing.

20:05.000 --> 20:07.000
They consist of two blocks.

20:08.000 --> 20:10.000
The main source of the enterprise's capital

20:11.000 --> 20:13.000
is the right balance amount of the left part.

20:14.000 --> 20:16.000
Moreover, it consists of the private assets

20:17.000 --> 20:19.000
as well as the obligations

20:20.000 --> 20:22.000
that the enterprise has

20:23.000 --> 20:25.000
in order to borrow some funds.

20:26.000 --> 20:28.000
So, private assets and obligations

20:29.000 --> 20:31.000
are equal to the assets.

20:32.000 --> 20:34.000
Passives are equal to the assets,

20:35.000 --> 20:37.000
and assets are equal to the amount

20:38.000 --> 20:40.000
of private assets and obligations.

20:41.000 --> 20:43.000
These are the requirements

20:44.000 --> 20:46.000
of each part of the accounting balance.

20:47.000 --> 20:49.000
Let's focus on the assets,

20:50.000 --> 20:52.000
on the left part.

20:53.000 --> 20:55.000
We will study them carefully

20:56.000 --> 20:58.000
and see what they are.

20:59.000 --> 21:01.000
I recommend you to take the balance

21:02.000 --> 21:04.000
and study it carefully,

21:05.000 --> 21:07.000
listen to the lecture and look at the balance.

21:08.000 --> 21:10.000
It will be easier for you to master it,

21:11.000 --> 21:13.000
to understand what it consists of,

21:14.000 --> 21:16.000
and to understand the meaning of the lines.

21:17.000 --> 21:19.000
Why are they written in one way or another?

21:20.000 --> 21:22.000
There is nothing random or chaotic in the balance.

21:23.000 --> 21:25.000
It contains the great logic

21:26.000 --> 21:28.000
of the financiers

21:29.000 --> 21:31.000
who prepared the balance.

21:32.000 --> 21:34.000
The assets of the enterprise

21:35.000 --> 21:37.000
are grouped by their liquidity.

21:38.000 --> 21:40.000
Liquidity means

21:41.000 --> 21:43.000
that the balance is not fixed

21:44.000 --> 21:46.000
and that it is possible

21:47.000 --> 21:49.000
to turn the assets into money.

21:50.000 --> 21:52.000
The more liquidity the asset is,

21:53.000 --> 21:55.000
the easier and faster

21:56.000 --> 21:58.000
it turns into money.

21:59.000 --> 22:01.000
It is clear that the most liquidity asset

22:02.000 --> 22:04.000
is the money assets.

22:05.000 --> 22:07.000
They are very easy to turn into money.

22:08.000 --> 22:10.000
Everything else

22:11.000 --> 22:13.000
requires a longer period

22:14.000 --> 22:16.000
of time to turn

22:17.000 --> 22:19.000
the assets into money.

22:20.000 --> 22:22.000
The lines of the asset

22:23.000 --> 22:25.000
are written from top to bottom

22:26.000 --> 22:28.000
according to the degree of liquidity.

22:29.000 --> 22:31.000
The top line

22:32.000 --> 22:34.000
is the least liquidity asset,

22:35.000 --> 22:37.000
the bottom line

22:38.000 --> 22:40.000
is the fastest liquidity asset.

22:41.000 --> 22:43.000
So, from top to bottom

22:44.000 --> 22:46.000
the assets are divided

22:47.000 --> 22:49.000
into two blocks.

